課程教材 Course Material
	    Lab handouts    

參考書目 References


備註 Remarks
     • Students are divided into 10 groups; basically 3-4 students form a group.
• You are strongly encouraged to preview ahead of the experiment. This is the only way that you can get the most out of the experiment.
• For each experiment, a leader should be elected by group members and he/she will be in charge of the whole experiment.
• The results should be validated (signed and dated) by the TA at the end of each experiment; this portion of your lab report can be duplicated among group members. Everyone, however, should submit their own report (no more than four A4-sized sheets) to the TA within one week after the experiment.
• Maintaining a good lab notebook is strongly encouraged and extra credit will be given. The lab notebook is due on 6/20; it will be returned to you after grading.
 




基本素養 Basic Literacy
□ 理解專業醫學與工程倫理及社會責任
 
■ 培養有效溝通、表達及團隊合作精神之能力
 
■ 培養終身學習的能力
 
□ 培養具備國際觀及外語能力
 
□ 永續環境、社會關懷與人文素養
 
 

核心能力 Competence
■ 活用與整合跨學科知識的能力
 
■ 瞭解解剖與生理等相關基礎醫學的知識
 
■ 瞭解數學、物理、化學等相關基礎科學的知識
 
■ 熟悉臨床醫學及醫療儀器與器材的問題
 
■ 設計與執行實驗，以及分析與解釋數據的能力
 
■ 執行生醫工程系統實務所需技術、技巧及相關醫學規範之能力
 
■ 培養跨領域生醫工程模擬與分析之能力
 
□ 研發及製造醫療儀器與器材之能力
 
 

課程概述 Course Description
       本課程主要在於建立醫學工程基本觀念，內容包括醫工與生物力學概論，步態分析，生醫感測器，醫用超音波，職業傷害與生物力學，輪椅驅動之生物力學，坐姿與 身體支撐物，肌電圖與信號處理，功能性電刺激，全人工髖關節生物力學，電腦繪圖應用於醫學工程，電阻抗影像技術，電腦斷層掃描技術，眼球運動，脊椎生物力 學。 

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    The objectives of this laboratory are
(1) To provide hand-on-experience of commonly used medical devices or related techniques in biomedical engineering,
(2) To learn to keep a good record of experiments and maintain a lab notebook,
(3) To stimulate the passion of development of new medical devices.
     

